com.mojang.datafixers.optics

Class Optic.CompositionOptic<Proof extends K1,S,T,A,B,A1,B1>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mojang.datafixers.optics.Optic.CompositionOptic<Proof,S,T,A,B,A1,B1>
  • Type Parameters:
    Proof - The profunctor type this optic evaluates. It shall be a subtype of the outer and inner optics' type.
    S - The input object type.
    T - The output object type.
    A - The input field type.
    B - The output field type.
    A1 - The input subfield type.
    B1 - The output subfield type.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Optic<Proof,S::A1,T::B1>
    Enclosing interface:
    Optic<Proof extends K1,S,T,A,B>

    public static final class Optic.CompositionOptic<Proof extends K1,S,T,A,B,A1,B1>
extends Object
implements Optic<Proof,S::A1,T::B1>
    An optic that represents the composition of two compatible optics. Two optics are compatible if
    1. The profunctor types the two optics use have a common subtype.
    2. The fields types of the first optic correspond to the object types of the second optic.

    The composition acts on the objects of the first optic and the fields of the second optic.
